National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan had a meeting with President Guillermo Lasso of Ecuador to discuss various important issues. These included security, climate change, counter-drug cooperation, and addressing the migration challenge in the Western Hemisphere. Sullivan emphasized the United States' dedication to working together with Ecuador to achieve sustainable and inclusive economic growth, through initiatives like the Americas Partnership for Economic Prosperity. They also discussed the importance of expanding lawful pathways for migrants as an alternative to dangerous smuggling operations. Sullivan expressed gratitude to President Lasso for his support for Ukraine and his leadership on Haiti at the UN Security Council.